				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Starting a cat bard....<a name="2715"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 2 03 9:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The kitty bard.  If you plan on being a melee type bard this is the race for you.  In the end it should not matter too much.  The things to watch for bards are dex and cha mainly.  Dex is the bards primary stat as it is checked in calculation of whether a song hits a missed note.  The dex will also help you when you start to duel wield.  Cha is used in checks with duration of a charm and whether or not is succesful.  Some will argue cha affects mez but i am not to convinced on that one but i will use my piccolo just to make sure it lands first time and will continue to land.
<br />

<br />
Most songs till lvl 40 are in shar val, you are missing your first mana song however which is sold in east commons, you will need to travel to get that one.  Might even be sold in PoK library now.
<br />

<br />
Kitty's are fine, it really comes to personal preference, just concentrate your starting points into your dex and you should be good.  Check eq.casterealm.com for good suggestions on starting stats for bard races.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
