				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Starting a cat bard....<a name="4383"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 03 10:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Where to start... So much info here. Thanks Gwiber!
<br />

<br />
Few things to clarify:
<br />

<br />
Stamina helps a fair amount with HPs, which are very nice to have especially when stunned while swarm kiting, or doing crowd control and the mez/charm breaks and they hate you for some reason.  Bards get very few decent stamina items that also effect our primary stats.
<br />

<br />
Speaking of primary stats, they are, as I've seen countless times, Dex, cha, int (sta and str for melee).
<br />

<br />
One thing to point out is Gwiber's discussion on CHA, it does not have anything to do with missed notes.  Missed notes are a function of your level in relation to the song level you are playing and dex will not only help your weapons proc, but will help you miss fewer notes.  I must say though that the recent patch increased our missed notes tremendously, another nerf from Sony that I've been told, is to justify the AA skill that lets you not miss notes.
<br />

<br />
Also on CHA, it is used heavily in charming. I am not sure on the particulars regarding length of charm or resists (I do know equiping your wind instrument helps on both resists and length), but it is the charm stat for sure.  I found I have no troubles swarm kiting now that I got my CHA over 150, before I sucked at it in PoD.
<br />

<br />
Thanks Gwiber, all around good post!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
