				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Starting a cat bard....<a name="4395"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 03 1:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think I understand why you were told to dump stats for AC/HP. After about 56 or 57, until 64 when you get a new charm, you are effectively relegated to chant kiting or grouping. Most bards group at that time as chant kiting a 20k hp mob is painfully slow and teadious, let alone the carpal tunnel (sp) issues, hehe.  If you are grouping, you want AC and HP for when you get beat on by mobs.  That's likely the reason to dump other stats (NEVER DEX though). It's not typical that we are asked to do crowd control, and even then, it's limited.
<br />

<br />
I too have dex rings, though mine are tied to cha as well for swarm kiting.  I also have the hp/ac rings for meleeing, as well as BD rings for raids (resists).  In fact I have almost 3 complete sets of armor on me for one reason or another. hehe.
<br />

<br />
Oh and as for CHA not hurting. I had no problems swarm kiting old world mobs either with a sub 100 or 110 CHA.  It wasn't til I went to Luclin (ME Toilers) and REALLY when I went to PoD (flies etc.) that I found my CHA lacking big time! I sunk 2k into Koada'Dal Mithril armor (dex/cha) and OMG did it make a HUGE difference.  There is a thread or two on that already so I won't go further.  Just an FYI.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
