				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Starting a cat bard....<a name="7603"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 27 03 1:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Cha works like this, the mob gets an intial resist vs. your charm that is based on it's MR, if it makes this check a second one is made vs. your Cha, if the mob makes both saves he is not charmed, if he failes either he is charmed.  The cha check is then made again at each tick of the song and if the mob makes the cha check it breaks free, which is why low Cha will result in shorter charm times... at least that's how a 65 chanter in my guild explained it to me but it could work different for our songs.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
