			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Starting a cat bard....<a name="8938"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 9 03 6:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>well, all I have to say is battlecat bards rock<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  And if you want to be a melee bard stamina is nice and dex is nice, but there are great hps buffs out there, and they last a really long time.  And anything over 100 dex is good for many many levels.  However more STR = more ATK points.  And if you want to hit things you need ATK maxed.  You not only hit harder with higher str but you hit a lot more often.  You can have a starting str of about 120 with a vah shir (I forget if that is exactly right, but it is close) and with a nice set of armor you can break 200.  That means early on with your battle buff songs you can well exceed 200 str, and you will be loving the melee.  Even later in levels druid/shamie str buffs are not always available, and they do not last as long as high end HP buffs, so even if you get one in PoK before you go fight it will be gone soon.  So all you can depend on for str really are you songs and your gear.  If you want to melee never go below 200 str is my advice.  Once you have your str maxed you can begin upgrading your armor to give you more AC, HPs, Stam and Dex.  But Str will help you more than any of those early on.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and since we are Int based for mana, please please do not put any into wisdom.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
